<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Voting_as_a_Security_Problem">Voting as a Security Problem</span></h2>
<p>voting is fundamental for democracy; electoral fraud is as old as voting</p>
<h4> <span class="mw-headline" id="Goals_for_the_course">Goals for the course</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>Understand how votes are counted</li>
<li>Apply the security mindset</li>
<li>Critically examine the role of technology</li>
<li>Learn what we can do to make elections more fair and accurate</li>
</ul>
<h4> <span class="mw-headline" id="Security_Mindset">Security Mindset</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>Look for ways that things can go wrong</li>
<li>Adversary = criminal, bad guy</li>
<li>Adversarial failures = adversary successfully sabatoging something</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Think like an attacker</strong>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><dl><dd><ul><li> Understand how to circumvent security
</li><li> How can the system break?
</li><li> What is the weakest link? easist to attack?
</li><li> Identify false assumptions
</li><li> Think outside the box of system designer</li></ul></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></p>
